ypt]]\n| 1848\n|\n| [[Cholera]]\n| <ref name=Kuhnke /><ref name=Gallagher/>\n|-\n|\n| [[North America]]\n| 1848\u20131849\n|\n| [[Cholera]]\n|\n|-\n|\n| [[United States]]\n| 1850\n|\n| [[Yellow fever]]\n|\n|-\n|\n| [[North America]]\n| 1850\u20131851\n|\n| [[Influenza]]\n|\n|-\n|\n| [[United States]]\n| 1851\n| \n| [[Cholera]]\n|<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Daly |first1=Walter J. |title=The Black Cholera Comes to the Central Valley of America in the 19th Century \u2013 1832, 1849, and Later |journal=Transactions of the American Clinical and Climatological Association |date=2008 |volume=119 |pages=143\u2013153 |issn=0065-7778|pmc=2394684 |pmid=18596846 }}</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[United States]]\n| 1852\n| \n| [[Yellow fever]]\n|\n|-\n| 1,000,000\n| [[Russia]]\n| 1852\u20131860\n| [[Third cholera pandemic]]\n| [[Cholera]]\n| <ref name=Hays2005/>\n|-\n|\n| [[Ottoman Empire]]\n| 1853\n| \n| [[Plague (disease)|Plague]]\n| <ref name=\"Practitioner\">{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=cWUCAAAAYAAJ |title=Practitioner |year=1877 |access-date=29 March 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| 4,737\n| [[Copenhagen]], [[Denmark]]\n| 1853\n| [[1853 Copenhagen cholera outbreak|Cholera epidemic of Copenhagen 1853]]\n| [[Cholera]]\n| <ref>[http://wayback-01.kb.dk/wayback/20100504134515/http://www2.kb.dk/udstillinger/medhist/kolera/efterhistorien.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150103085703/http://wayback-01.kb.dk/wayback/20100504134515/http://www2.kb.dk/udstillinger/medhist/kolera/efterhistorien.html |date=2015-01-03 }} About Cholera epidemic of Copenhagen 1853</ref>\n|-\n| 616\n| [[England]]\n| 1854\n| [[Broad Street cholera outbreak]]\n| [[Cholera]]\n| <ref name=\"Snow1855\">{{Cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/b28985266 |title=On the mode of communication of cholera |last=John Snow |publisher=John Churchill |year=1855 |access-date=29 March 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n| [[United States]]\n| 1855\n|\n| [[Yellow fever]]\n|\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"12,000,000\"|>12 million in I