1028791 |title=DR Congo measles: More than 6,000 dead in world's worst outbreak |language=en |access-date=2020-02-28 |work=BBC News |date=2020-01-08 |}}</ref>\n|-\n|83\n|[[Samoa]]\n|2019\u2013present\n|[[2019 Samoa measles outbreak]]\n|[[Measles]]\n|<ref name=\"Samoa83\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/406802/two-more-deaths-from-measles-in-samoa-over-new-year-period|title=Two more deaths from measles in samoa over new year period|last=|first=|date=2020-01-07|work=Radio New Zealand|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200107105921/https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/406802/two-more-deaths-from-measles-in-samoa-over-new-year-period|archive-date=2020-01-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2,000\" | > 2,000\n|[[Asia-Pacific]], [[Latin America]]\n|2019\u2013present\n|[[2019\u201320 dengue fever epidemic]]\n|[[Dengue fever]]\n|<ref>{{cite news |title=Dengue and severe dengue |url=https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/dengue-and-severe-dengue |work=World Health Organization (WHO) |date=2 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2019/12/17/788965365/why-dengue-fever-cases-are-hitting-record-highs-in-latin-america|title=Why Dengue Fever Cases Are Hitting Record Highs In Latin America|work=NPR|date=19 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=WHO says 2019 'worse than usual' for dengue in Pacific|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/397502/who-says-2019-worse-than-usual-for-dengue-in-pacific|date=26 August 2019|publisher=[[Radio New Zealand]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"114,200+\" | 177,424 (As of April 22, 2020)\n| [[World|Worldwide]] \n| 2019\u2013present\n| [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n|[[COVID-19|COVID-19 / SARS-CoV-2]]\n| <ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2020/02/the-latest-coronavirus-cases/|title=Tracking coronavirus: Map, data and timeline|date=2 February 2020|work=Bnonews|access-date=16 February 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|publisher=bnonews.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 |title = Operations Dashboard for ArcGIS}}</ref>\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/|title=(Coronavirus Update live): 191,127 Cases and 7,807 Deaths 978,328,090 Recovered from 2019 \u2013 Ncov Virus Outbreak \u2013 Worldometer|website=www.worldometers.info|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{portal|Pandemic}}\n*{{annotated link|List of Ebola outbreaks}}\n*{{annotated link|History of smallpox}}\n*{{annotated link|Timeline of plague}}\n*{{annotated link|Timeline of cholera}}\n*{{annotated link|Globalization and disease}}\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|3|refs=\n<ref name=\"Pryor\">{{Cite journal |last=Pryor |first=E. G. |year=1975 |title=The great plague of Hong Kong |journal=Journal of the Hong Kong Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society |volume=15 |pages=61\u201370 |jstor=23881624 |pmid=11614750}}</ref>\nhttps://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/feb/13/coronavirus-latest-updates-deaths-in-china-pass-1300-with-jump-in-cases-live-news\n<ref name=\"Harbin Plague\">{{Cite web |url=http://news.sina.com.cn/c/sd/2011-01-14/130221815935.shtml |title=In Memory of the 1910 Harbin Plague |access-date=2011-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028165551/http://news.sina.com.cn/c/sd/2011-01-14/130221815935.shtml |archive-date=2017-10-28 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Patterson1\">{{Cite journal |last=Patterson |first=K. D. |last2=Pyle |first2=G. F. |year=1991 |title=The geography and mortality of the 1918 influenza pandemic |journal=Bulletin of the History of Medicine |volume=65 |issue=1 |pages=4\u201321 |pmid=2021692}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"1911e\">{{cite EB1911 |wstitle=Plague |volume=21 |pages=693\u2013705}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"DSHS\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/preparedness/bt_public_history_plague.shtm |title=Texas Department of State Health Services, History of Plague |access-date=2008-07-01 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HfryBSov?url=http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/preparedness/bt_public_history_plague.shtm |archive-date=2013-06-26 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Faruque et al 2005\">{{Cite journal |last=Faruque |first=S. M. |last2=Islam |first2=M. J. |last3=Ahmad |first3=Q. S. |last4=Faruque |first4=A. S. G. |last5=Sack |first5=D. A. |last6=Nair |first6=G. B. |last7=Mekalanos |first7=J. J. |year=2005 |title=Self-limiting nature of seasonal cholera epidemics: Role of host-mediated amplification of phage |journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences |volume=102 |issue=17 |pages=6119\u20136124 |bibcode=2005PNAS..102.6119F |doi=10.1073/pnas.0502069102 |pmc=1087956 |pmid=15829587}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"WHOint\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2004/pr55/en/ |title=World Health Organization action in Afghanistan aims to control debilitating leishmaniasis |access-date=16 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171012030854/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2004/pr55/en/ |archive-date=12 October 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{Cite journal |last=Hunter |first=Philip |year=2007 |title=Inevitable or avoidable? Despite the lessons of history, the world is not yet ready to face the next great plague |journal=EMBO Reports |volume=8 |issue=6 |pages=531\u2013534 |doi=10.1038/sj.embor.7400987 |pmc=2002527 |pmid=17545992}}\n* {{cite journal | last1=Pacheco | first1=Daniela Alexandra de Meneses Rocha | last2=Rodrigues | first2=Ac\u00e1cio Agostinho Gon\u00e7alves | last3=Silva | first3=Carmen Maria Lisboa da | title=Ebola virus \u2013 from neglected threat to global emergency state | journal=Revista da Associa\u00e7\u00e3o M\u00e9dica Brasileira |  date=October 2016 | volume=62 | issue=5|pages=458\u2013467 | doi=10.1590/1806-9282.62.05.458 | pmid=27656857 }